Prescribed understory fire for oak regeneration could be used in the future to increase habitat suitability for this species.
The MNF participates with WVDNR in annual monitoring of this species.
The one small whorled pogonia site on the MNF is surveyed annually.
It has not been found in the last few years.
About 5000 MNF acres of white pine, low elevation ecological landtypes of LTA Bd03 (DeMeo, 1998) have been surveyed for this species.
Also, all proposed project areas across the MNF have been surveyed for this species before a project is implemented.
No new sites have been found.
